author: Nba Australia
title: WATCH: Thon Maker has 12 points, 3 blocks in Bucks loss to Jazz | NBA | Sporting News
text:
February 2, 2017 2:21am EST February 2, 2017 12:05am EST The young Aussie impressed in his third start. NBA Australia 
Published on Feb. 2, 2017 
Updated at 2:21 a.m. ET 
Rookie Thon Maker produced his best performance of the season, finishing with 12 points, five rebounds and three blocks in the Milwaukee Bucks' 104-88 loss to the Utah Jazz. 
MORE: Cavs interested in Melo if Love not involved 
Going toe-to-toe with Jazz big man Rudy Gobert, who finished with 26 points and 15 rebounds, Maker showed flashes of his potential, expecially on the defensive end. 
Utah dominated the second quarter, with Gobert scoring 15 of the teams 31 points in the period as they took a 61-43 lead into halftime. 
Milwaukee only managed 16 points in the quarter and never recovered from there Thon's top plays from tonight as he dropped 12 points and swatted 3 shots against the Jazz!! #OwnTheFuture pic.twitter.com/kjEZFMuURf â€” Milwaukee Bucks (@Bucks) February 2, 2017 
The game was a special one for Aussie fans, with four players represented between both teams. 
Matthew Dellavedova chipped in five points and seven assists, while Joe Ingles and Dante Exum both had relatively quiet nights for the Jazz.
